STATE OF TENNESSEE, etc., v. Hon. George C. TAYLOR, U. S. District Judge. No. 10706. United States Court of Appeals Sixth Circuit. May 31, 1949. James B. Wright, Knoxville, Tenn., George G. Allen, Sevierville, Tenn., for petitioner. Respondent not represented.

Before SIMONS, ALLEN, and MARTIN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It appearing to the court that no steps having been taken in this case since July-13, 1948, 169 E.2d 626.

It is now ordered that this case be and the same is dismissed with leave to reinstate for good cause shown.
